name: r-gridtext
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.1.4" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-gridtext
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/gridtext_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/gridtext/gridtext_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c1cca9c68c6de4095546d2dab0ffff1d6e4fcf9ca2b9e878dc7a7237ede1338c

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcurl
    - r-rcpp
    - r-jpeg
    - r-markdown
    - r-png
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr
    - r-systemfonts
    - r-xml2
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcurl
    - r-rcpp
    - r-jpeg
    - r-markdown
    - r-png
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr
    - r-systemfonts
    - r-xml2

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('gridtext')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('gridtext')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://wilkelab.org/gridtext
  license: MIT
  summary: Provides support for rendering of formatted text using 'grid' graphics. Text can be formatted via a minimal subset of 'Markdown', 'HTML', and inline 'CSS' directives, and it can be rendered both with and without word wrap.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: gridtext
# Type: Package

# Version: 0.1.0
